// Configuration (EDIT ME)
// One item per endpoint to keep warm. Point these at the PUBLIC health URLs of
// the services you want to stop from spinning down (the gateway, and the PDF
// service if you render PDFs). /health needs no API key and bypasses every gate.
//
// IMPORTANT - Render free tier: each workspace gets 750 instance-hours/MONTH,
// shared across ALL your free services, and spun-down time does NOT count. One
// service kept awake 24/7 is ~730h - already almost the whole budget. Keeping two
// services awake around the clock (~1460h) blows past 750 and Render SUSPENDS them
// until next month. That is why the schedule above is work-hours-only (Mon-Fri,
// 07-19 in your n8n's timezone => ~290h/service/month). Widen it only if you know
// you have the hours, or if these services are on a PAID plan (paid never sleeps,
// so you don't need this workflow at all).
return [
  { json: { url: 'https://YOUR-GATEWAY.onrender.com/health' } },
  // { json: { url: 'https://YOUR-PDF-SERVICE.onrender.com/health' } },
];
